en_205336_0	The Consumer Affairs Authority stated that island wide raids will be carried out in search of traders who violate consumer laws during the festive season.
en_205336_1	Accordingly, island-wide raids will be carried out until the 15th of January.
en_205336_2	Focus will be paid on irregularities in markets including overpriced goods and expired goods.
en_205336_3	The Consumer Affairs Authority stated that it will be urging traders to display the prices of goods.
en_205336_4	The Consumer Affairs Authority has carried out 21,000 raids thus far this year and has taken legal action against 20,000.
en_205336_5	The Authority noted that fines amounting to nearly 85 million rupees have been imposed on the convicts.
